---
title: Order Microgreens
description: Order arugula, broccoli, radish, pea tendril and 6 more microgreens at $3.50/oz. Weekly delivery to Lake Mary, Sanford, Winter Park, Oviedo, Casselberry, Maitland, and Downtown Orlando.
permalink: /microgreens/
layout: default
greens:
  -
    name: Arugula
    id: arugula
    fact: Bold and peppery — a handful turns plain eggs, pizza, or a sandwich into something restaurant-worthy.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Beet
    id: beet
    fact: Earthy-sweet with bright pink stems. Beautiful on goat cheese toast, grain bowls, and roasted veggie plates.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Broccoli
    id: broccoli
    fact: Up to 40x the sulforaphane of mature broccoli. Mild flavor — sneak it into smoothies, eggs, or anywhere.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Cilantro
    id: cilantro
    fact: All the cilantro punch, none of the chopping. Tacos, pho, guac, salsa verde — taco Tuesday upgraded.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Kale
    id: kale
    fact: Milder and sweeter than full-grown kale, and loaded with vitamin K. Great on avocado toast and grain bowls.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Kohlrabi
    id: kohlrabi
    fact: Crisp, mild, slightly broccoli-sweet. Packed with vitamin C — perfect on slaws, sandwiches, and noodle bowls.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Mustard
    id: mustard
    fact: A horseradish-y kick that wakes up sandwiches, deviled eggs, and roast beef. Aids digestion, too.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Pea Tendril
    id: pea
    fact: Sweet, crisp, like fresh-shelled peas. Loaded with potassium — gorgeous in stir-fries, ramen, and salads.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Radish
    id: radish
    fact: Spicy crunch that cuts through rich foods. Tacos, banh mi, avocado toast, ramen — instant upgrade.
    amount: 4
  -
    name: Swiss Chard
    id: chard
    fact: Tender, mild, with neon-pink stems. Rich in magnesium — wilt into pasta or scatter raw on plated dishes.
    amount: 4
locations:
  -
    id: far_north_orlando
    area: Lake Mary, Sanford, Winter Springs, Oviedo
    days: Friday mornings
  -
    id: north_orlando
    area: Casselberry, Maitland, Winter Park, College Park
    days: Monday & Wednesday evenings
  -
    id: downtown
    area: Downtown
    days: Sunday afternoons
---
<form action="https://formsubmit.co/micros@volkman.farm" method="post">
  <input type="hidden" name="_next" value="https://volkman.farm/thanks/">
  <input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="New microgreens order">
  <input type="text" name="_honey" style="display:none">
  <p>Hey neighbor! We grow ten varieties of microgreens right here in Orlando — harvested the morning we deliver to you. $3.50/oz, pay on delivery (Venmo, Zelle, or cash). Let's get you started.</p>
  <p>First — where are we delivering? We only run one route per neighborhood per week, so this tells us which day works.</p>
  <p>
    <select id="location" name="location" required>
      <option disabled selected value> -- pick a location -- </option>
      {% for location in locations %}
      <optgroup label="{{ location.days }}">
        <option value="{{ location.id }}">{{ location.area }}</option>
      </optgroup>
      {% endfor %}
    </select>
  </p>
  <div id="step2" style="display:none">
    <p>Great — we'll see you there. Which green would you like to start with? <a href="/greens/">Read about each variety →</a></p>
    <p>
      <select id="greens" name="green" required>
        <option disabled selected value> -- pick a green -- </option>
        {% for green in greens %}
        <option value="{{ green.id }}">{{ green.name }}</option>
        {% endfor %}
      </select>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div id="step3" style="display:none">
    <p><span id="fact"></span></p>
    <p>Most neighbors start with <span id="amount"></span>oz of <span id="green"></span> a week — enough to top dinners for two without anything going to waste. How much sounds right?</p>
    <p>
      <select id="amount-select" name="amount-select" required>
        <option disabled selected value> -- pick an amount -- </option>
        {% for i in (1..8) %}
        <option value="{{ i }}">{{ i }}oz</option>
        {% endfor %}
      </select>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div id="step4" style="display:none">
    <p>Last step. Drop your phone and email — we'll text you to confirm your first delivery day and the exact total. No subscription, no auto-charge, cancel any week.</p>
    <p>
      <input id="phone" name="phone" type="tel" size="46" placeholder="867-5309" required>
    </p>
    <p>
      <input id="email" name="email" type="email" size="46" placeholder="crazy@about.microgreens" required>
    </p>
    <p>
      <input id="standing" type="checkbox" name="standing_order" value="yes">
      <label for="standing">Make this a <a href="/subscribe/">weekly standing order</a> — 10% off, skip any week.</label>
    </p>
    <p>
      <input id="consent" type="checkbox" name="consent" required>
      <label for="consent">Okay to text and email me about my order and weekly availability.</label>
    </p>
    <p>
      <input type="submit" value="Send my order">
    </p>
  </div>
</form>

<script>
  const greens = [{%- for green in greens -%}{ id: "{{ green.id }}", name: "{{ green.name }}", fact: "{{ green.fact }}", amount: "{{ green.amount }}" },{%- endfor -%}];

  document.getElementById('location').addEventListener('change', () => {
    document.getElementById('step2').style.display = 'block';
  });

  document.getElementById('greens').addEventListener('change', e => {
    const green = greens.find(g => g.id == e.target.value);
    document.getElementById('fact').innerText = green.fact;
    document.getElementById('amount').innerText = green.amount;
    document.getElementById('green').innerText = green.name;
    document.getElementById('step3').style.display = 'block';
  });

  document.getElementById('amount-select').addEventListener('change', () => {
    document.getElementById('step4').style.display = 'block';
  });
</script>
